entire bill and insert
14
15 “An Act relating to agriculture; requiring persons
entering certain areas to maintain position of the
16 gate at use; prescribing penalties for violation;
providing for promulgation of rules; providing for
17 codification; and providing an effective date.
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2-34 of Title 2, unless there is
22 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23
24
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 1356 Page 1
1 A. Any individual entering through gates used for ingress or
2 egress to a property designated as an easement shall maintain the
3 position of the gate upon use.
4 B. 1. Any individual who violates the provisions of subsection
5 A of this section shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a misdemeanor
6 punishable by a fine not more than Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00),
7 by imprisonment in a county jail for not more than ninety (90) days,
8 or by both such fine and imprisonment.
9 2. Any individual convicted of a second offense shall, upon
10 conviction, be guilty of a misdemeanor punishable by a fine not more
11 than One Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00), by imprisonment in a county
12 jail for not more than one hundred eighty (180) days, or by both
13 such fine and imprisonment.
14 3. Any individual convicted of a third or subsequent offense
15 shall, upon conviction, be punished by a fine not more than One
16 Thousand Five Hundred Dollars ($1,500.00), by imprisonment in a
17 county jail for not more than one (1) year, or by both such fine and
18 imprisonment.
19 4. Any individual convicted pursuant to the provisions of this
20 subsection shall also be liable for damages.
21 C. The Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry
22 shall promulgate rules necessary to implement the provisions of this
23 act.
24 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.”
